ðŸ§­ Number-by-number walk-through
#	Code fragment	Plain-English explanation
1	request.getData().stream()	Start with every record in the incoming request.
.filter(rec -> validationTable.equalsIgnoreCase(rec.getEntity()))	Keep only the records that belong to the table weâ€™re validating (e.g. â€œLOANâ€).
.flatMap(rec -> rec.getAttributeData().stream())	Dive one level deeper: turn each recordâ€™s attribute map into a flat stream so we can touch each column value individually.
.forEach(attr -> { â€¦ })	Handle every attribute map one by one.
if (queryUtil.multiColumnValuesValidation(attr, columnSpec))	Check that every piece of the composite key exists and is non-empty.
*(columnSpec is something like `"REGION
